node.title: Onlookers delighted as dolphins make a splash at jazz concert
node.description: A curious dolphin has delighted onlookers during a jazz concert at an underwater observatory. And it's not the first time marine creatures have crashed the party.
node.content:
["The music of jazz singers like Ella Fitzgerald, Louis Armstrong and Nat King Cole has found a new legion of unlikely underwater fans after\u00a0a group of dolphins put on a surprise\u00a0show for\u00a0concertgoers at an underwater observatory in Western Australia's south-west.", "The audience watched on in delight at a\u00a0concert hosted at Busselton Jetty\u00a0when a curious dolphin swam around the observatory's windows and jetty pylons.\u00a0", "The venue's environment manager Sophie Teede said it looked like the dolphin was 'enjoying the music'.", "She said the close encounter\u00a0was a rare occurrence, but not the first time it has\u00a0happened.\u00a0", "\"I've worked at the jetty now for quite some time, and on a regular day to day basis we almost never see dolphins \u2014 probably less than a handful of times over the last ten years,\" Ms Teede said.\u00a0", "\"So, to see them at the observatory on both of the jazz events over the last two months is pretty unusual,\" she said.", "Ms Teede said the dolphins were probably investigating the underwater sounds.", "\"\"The large dolphin also looked like she was pregnant so she definitely wouldn't have been putting herself in any danger at all,\" she said.\u00a0", "", "
Could dolphins be\u00a0fans of jazz music?(Supplied: Murdoch University Cetacean Research Unit)
", "As to whether this pointed to dolphins being a fan of jazz or if they would have preferred some more contemporary music, Ms\u00a0Teede wasn't sure.", "\"Taylor Swift might be a go. Maybe some more upbeat house music?\" she laughed.", "She said the Busselton Jetty team would further investigate\u00a0the impact of underwater sound.", "\"We'll definitely look to get some more sound recorders in and see what we can discover there.\"\u00a0", "
Educational opportunity\u00a0
", "Associate professor at Edith Cowan University Chandra Salgado Kent said the dolphins were most likely curious about the jazz music.", "\"It looked amazing, and it looks like there are a lot of people in the room that were having an experience that many other people won't have,\" she said.", "\"I imagine that that particular individual may have been curious about the sound and come up to have a look.", "\"Animals are attracted or deterred for different reasons.\"\u00a0", "", "
Chandra Salgado Kent says the dolphins were probably just curious.\u00a0(Supplied:\u00a0Dr Chandra Salgado Kent\u00a0)
", "She said the impacts of underwater sound on animals wasn't always positive.", "\"With vessels, particularly commercial fishing vessels ...\u00a0dolphins can learn to go to those boats because they hear it and try to get a meal out of it,\" she said.\u00a0", "\"In those cases, it can actually put them at risk of harm\".", "Dr\u00a0Salgado Kent said these events help to create more awareness and education about marine life.\u00a0", "\"I think that more and more, as these sorts of venues develop, that it's an amazing opportunity ... to be able to communicate conservation messages and give people the opportunity to experience something very unique and walk away understanding a lot more about these animals,\" she said."]
